subsection.p:
Here's the cartoon for a surjective linear transformation.  It is meant to suggest that for every output in $V$ there is at least one input in $U$ that is sent to the output.  (Even though we have depicted several inputs sent to each output.)  The key feature of this cartoon is that there are no vectors in $V$ without an arrow pointing to them.

